_source.productName: Brisbane Ballet presents Aquila Double Bill
_source.productDescription:
Immerse yourself in an evening of breathtaking dance with Brisbane Ballet's captivating double bill, Aquila. Prepare for an unforgettable evening of heart-stirring performances that will evoke a spectrum of emotions, from profound sadness to radiant joy. Be ready to be spellbound.

Morbus is a soul-stirring modern ballet that weaves a tragic tale of forbidden love, divine retribution, and enduring sorrow. Set to the transcendent music of J.S. Bach, Handel, Purcell, Rameau, and Vivaldi, with choreography by Emrys Goldsworthy, the ballet unfolds the story of a fallen angel who, captivated by a human woman, defies divine will to love her. Condemned by God for his transgression, their children are cursed with disease and death as a merciless punishment. 

In the Shadow of Love is a poignant modern ballet inspired by William Shakespeare's Sonnet 144, weaving a tragic narrative of love lost, betrayal, and unfulfilled devotion. Set to the haunting, minimalist music of Arvo PÃ¤rt, with choreography by Emrys Goldsworthy, the ballet reimagines the sonnet's love triangle through a contemporary lens: a woman and man meet and fall deeply in love, but her discovery of a fatal illness leads her to entrust a friend with a message of her love and impending death. The friend, consumed by her own desire for the man, betrays her, pursuing him and leaving the woman's love to fade in the shadows.

Immergetevi in una serata di danza mozzafiato con l'affascinante doppio spettacolo del Brisbane Ballet, Aquila. Preparatevi a una serata indimenticabile con spettacoli emozionanti che evocheranno un ampio spettro di emozioni, dalla profonda tristezza alla gioia radiosa. Preparatevi a rimanere incantati.

Morbus Ã¨ un balletto moderno toccante che intreccia una tragica storia di amore proibito, punizione divina e dolore immenso. Sulle note trascendenti di J.S. Bach, HÃ¤ndel, Purcell, Rameau e Vivaldi, con la coreografia di Emrys Goldsworthy, il balletto racconta la storia di un angelo caduto che, affascinato da una donna umana, sfida la volontÃ  divina di amarla. Condannati da Dio per la sua trasgressione, i loro figli sono maledetti dalla malattia e dalla morte come punizione spietata.

"In the Shadow of Love" Ã¨ un toccante balletto moderno ispirato al Sonetto 144 di William Shakespeare, che intreccia una tragica narrazione di amore perduto, tradimento e devozione insoddisfatta. Sulle note inquietanti e minimaliste di Arvo PÃ¤rt, con le coreografie di Emrys Goldsworthy, il balletto reinterpreta il triangolo amoroso del sonetto attraverso una lente contemporanea: una donna e un uomo si incontrano e si innamorano profondamente, ma la scoperta di una malattia mortale la porta ad affidare a un'amica un messaggio d'amore e di morte imminente. L'amica, consumata dal desiderio per l'uomo, la tradisce, inseguendolo e lasciando che l'amore della donna svanisca nell'ombra.

Benamkan diri Anda dalam malam tari yang memukau bersama Brisbane Ballet, Aquila, dalam pertunjukan ganda yang memukau. Bersiaplah untuk malam tak terlupakan dengan pertunjukan yang menggetarkan hati dan akan membangkitkan beragam emosi, mulai dari kesedihan mendalam hingga kegembiraan yang membara. Bersiaplah untuk terpesona.

Morbus adalah balet modern yang menggetarkan jiwa, merangkai kisah tragis cinta terlarang, pembalasan ilahi, dan duka yang tak kunjung usai. Diiringi musik transenden karya J.S. Bach, Handel, Purcell, Rameau, dan Vivaldi, dengan koreografi oleh Emrys Goldsworthy, balet ini mengungkap kisah seorang malaikat jatuh yang terpikat oleh seorang perempuan manusia, menentang kehendak ilahi untuk mencintainya. Dikutuk oleh Tuhan atas pelanggarannya, anak-anak mereka dikutuk dengan penyakit dan kematian sebagai hukuman yang tak kenal ampun.

In the Shadow of Love adalah balet modern yang menyentuh hati, terinspirasi oleh Soneta 144 karya William Shakespeare, merangkai narasi tragis tentang cinta yang hilang, pengkhianatan, dan pengabdian yang tak terpenuhi. Diiringi musik minimalis Arvo PÃ¤rt yang menghantui, dengan koreografi karya Emrys Goldsworthy, balet ini menata ulang cinta segitiga soneta tersebut melalui sudut pandang kontemporer: seorang perempuan dan laki-laki bertemu dan jatuh cinta, tetapi penemuannya akan penyakit fatal mendorongnya untuk menitipkan pesan cinta dan ajalnya kepada seorang sahabat. Sahabat itu, yang dikuasai oleh hasratnya sendiri terhadap laki-laki itu, mengkhianatinya, mengejarnya, dan meninggalkan cinta perempuan itu dalam bayang-bayang.

_source.productDescription:
A triumph! A spectacle! A fuzzy wuzzy cuddle puddle! CatVideoFest is all that and more. 

After sell-out screenings in 2024, the quirky film event returns to Dendy Cinemas fur one special outdoor screening. _source.productDescription:
Top Dog Film Festival 2025: A Celebration of Canine Connections.

Experience the magic of dogs on the big screen at the 2025 Top Dog Film Festival - a heartwarming showcase of the extraordinary bond between canines and humans.

From clever concierge canines to loyal companions who transform lives, this festival brings you touching stories of remarkable dogs and the people who love them. Watch dedicated individuals working to improve the lives of your four-legged friends, and prepare to have your heart stolen by some incredibly clever canines.

This two-plus-hour cinematic celebration features a carefully curated collection of short films from independent filmmakers worldwide, capturing delightful moments that showcase the joy, loyalty, and unconditional love that make dogs your most treasured companions.

Join an unforgettable journey through the most inspirational, heartwarming, and entertaining canine stories from around the globe.

Get your tickets before they all sell out â you'd be barking mad to miss it.

One screening only.

Seating is not allocated.Â  Arrive early for the best seats.Â Â Sorry No Refunds.

This program is exempt from rating but would be considered a PG program.

_source.productDescription:
The Opera that inspired Moulin Rouge! and Rent The Musical.

Experience the original bohemian love story with Opera Australia.

On a freezing Christmas Eve, love sparks. Two hands meet in the dark and four friendsâ lives change forever.

When MimÃ¬ meets Rodolfo, itâs love at first touch. They head out to bustling CafÃ© Momus, where the feisty Musetta and Marcello rekindle their relationship. But even the deepest love canât warm a freezing winter.

For our bohemians, everything is possible and the future canât come quickly enough. Rodolfo and his friends are determined to make their mark on the world and experience everything it has to offer â but right now theyâd settle for something warm to eat.

Some emotions are too big for words alone, and for that, we have music. La BohÃ¨me exposes your soul to the feelings that only music can express.

The music soars with the ecstasy of love, crackles with the pain of jealousy and cries with the agony of loss.

Pucciniâs score has always captured the soaring spirit of young love, and this new production breathes fresh life into one of the worldâs favourite operas. Award-winning director Dean Bryant (Anything Goes, Sweet Charity) brings his trademark wit and vivacity to this new staging, which captures that giddy moment where you and your friends feel youâll live forever.

Opera yang menginspirasi Moulin Rouge! dan Rent The Musical.

Rasakan kisah cinta bohemian asli dengan Opera Australia.

Pada Malam Natal yang dingin, cinta bersemi. Dua tangan bertemu dalam kegelapan dan kehidupan empat sahabat berubah selamanya.

Ketika MimÃ¬ bertemu Rodolfo, itu adalah cinta pada sentuhan pertama. Mereka pergi ke CafÃ© Momus yang ramai, tempat Musetta dan Marcello yang bersemangat menghidupkan kembali hubungan mereka. Namun, bahkan cinta yang terdalam pun tidak dapat menghangatkan musim dingin yang dingin.

Bagi kaum bohemian, segalanya mungkin dan masa depan tidak akan datang cukup cepat. Rodolfo dan teman-temannya bertekad untuk meninggalkan jejak mereka di dunia dan merasakan semua yang ditawarkannya â tetapi saat ini mereka akan puas dengan sesuatu yang hangat untuk dimakan.

Beberapa emosi terlalu besar untuk diungkapkan dengan kata-kata saja, dan untuk itu, kita punya musik. La BohÃ¨me memaparkan jiwa Anda pada perasaan yang hanya dapat diungkapkan oleh musik.

Musiknya membumbung tinggi dengan kegembiraan cinta, berderak dengan rasa sakit karena cemburu, dan menangis dengan penderitaan karena kehilangan.

Musik latar Puccini selalu menangkap semangat cinta muda yang membumbung tinggi, dan produksi baru ini memberikan kehidupan baru ke dalam salah satu opera favorit dunia. Sutradara pemenang penghargaan Dean Bryant (Anything Goes, Sweet Charity) menghadirkan kecerdasan dan keceriaan khasnya ke pementasan baru ini, yang menangkap momen membahagiakan saat Anda dan teman-teman merasa akan hidup selamanya.

_source.productName: Australia Zoo Markets
_source.productDescription:
Come and experience the Australia Zoo Markets! By attending this fun community event you'll be supporting the vital conservation projects of Wildlife Warriors, including the Australia Zoo Wildlife Hospital. 

Get ready for a wild time with live entertainment, a jumping castle, delicious food trucks, and a treasure trove of market stalls! From handcrafted artisan products and stylish homewares to  Irwin family goodies, the Australia Zoo Markets have it all!

Don't forget to drop by the Wildlife Warrior market stall to get your raffle tickets to win some ripper prizes!

Visit the website for more information and mark your calendars. Join a day filled with excitement, laughter, and fantastic finds. See you at car park 1 at Australia Zoo!
_source.productShortDescription: Come and experience the Australia Zoo Markets!

Kings Beach Bar presents Flavours of the Coast â The Next Wave.

In 2024, The Beach Bars introduced Flavours of the Coast, an epic sold out degustation event! This year, they're letting locals pick their favourite Beach Bar venue for Flavours of the Coast â the Next Wave!

Choose from Cotton Tree Beach Bar, Coolum Beach Bar or Kings Beach Bar to experience a flavour sensation like no other, featuring local produce sourced from the Sunshine Coast region.

Each of their beautiful locations allow you to enjoy unrivalled waterfront views and an atmosphere where you can drift through the evening, immersing yourself in the best hospitality experience the Sunshine Coast has to offer.

_source.productName: 10 Years
_source.productDescription:
Muses Trio presents an exquisite selection of music from their latest album 10 Years, celebrating their first decade together. Since their debut in 2013, the Muses have committed to bringing women composers, their works and personal stories into the spotlight. 10 Years celebrates over a decade of the trio's advocacy for equal representation in the field.

This ABC Classic FM Feature Album champions new, enchanting works by leading Australian composers Nat Bartsch, Louise Denson, Ella Macens, Sally Greenaway and Elena Kats-Chernin, which will be brought to audiences live at Anywhere Festival this year.

Experience the intimacy and connection of this moving performance in the charming Brisbane Latvian Hall, tucked away in the side streets of Woolloongabba. Proceeds will go towards funding Muses Trio's next studio album.

Free parking on site and in neighbouring streets. Join friends for a drink at the cash bar, mingle with the artists after the show.

Il Muses Trio presenta una squisita selezione musicale dal suo ultimo album "10 Years", celebrando il loro primo decennio insieme. Fin dal loro debutto nel 2013, le Muses si sono impegnate a portare alla ribalta le compositrici, le loro opere e le loro storie personali. "10 Years" celebra oltre un decennio di impegno del trio per la paritÃ  di rappresentanza nel settore.

Questo speciale album di ABC Classic FM promuove nuove e incantevoli opere di importanti compositori australiani come Nat Bartsch, Louise Denson, Ella Macens, Sally Greenaway ed Elena Kats-Chernin, che saranno presentate al pubblico dal vivo all'Anywhere Festival di quest'anno.

Parcheggio gratuito in loco e nelle vie limitrofe. Unisciti agli amici per un drink al bar a pagamento e socializza con gli artisti dopo lo spettacolo.

_source.productName: Education Fair - Sunshine Coast 2025
_source.productDescription:
The Education Fair is Southeast Queensland's leading education expo.

Bringing together providers from every stage of a childâs learning journey under one roof, it is an unmissable event for anyone considering their child's education.

With plenty of demonstrations, entertainment, hands-on activities and 'come and try' sessions, it's a fair, an expo and a heap of free fun for kids!

Education providers from across SE QLD under one roof
Come & try sessions
Sensory play
Inflatable soccer arena
Robotics and STEAM spaces
Kids' workshops
Hands-on demonstrations
Food trucks and entertainment

Entry and all activities are free! Registration is essential.

_source.productDescription:
Queen & David Bowie are both music icons whose paths crossed in the 1980s when they collaborated on the hit song âUnder Pressureâ

Coming off the back of their 2024 Asian Tour âUnder Pressureâ brings together two of Australiaâs most sort after Tribute Shows - The Killer Queen Experience and The David Bowie Show, starring John Blunt renowned worldwide for his resemblance to Freddie Mercury and Wayne Vitale known as the voice of David Bowie. 

This live performance will showcase the greatest hits (and costumes) from both artists with The David Bowie Show opening the night with songs such as Letâs Dance, Heroâs, Space Oddity, Changes, Ashes to Ashes, China Girl and many more. 

Killer Queen will deliver the full Experience performing all of Queen's greatest hits including â Bohemian Rhapsody, We Will Rock You, We Are the Champions, Somebody to Love, Radio Ga Ga, Another One Bites the Dust and more in this 2 hour show not to be missed.

_source.productName: Vision Boarding: Art Meets Mindfulness
_source.productDescription:
Art meets mindfulness.  Join Rothy Benson for "an awesome opportunity to learn and grow" in a "really creative and friendly environment".

Vision Boarding is a fun technique about deeply exploring aspects of the 'self'.  The process gives you fascinating and insightful creations and takes you on a voyage of discovery and insight.

In this small-group session you will create a poster of your dreams, aspirations, or any chosen aspect of YOU. Through collage art, cutting words and pictures from magazines, plus a free-flow of visual ideas from your sub-conscious, you will build a unique picture of your topic, which then becomes a pleasing affirmation for the future.

This is a totally engrossing session which provides you with many long-term benefits of direction and motivation.

Anyone can do this, you don't need to be an Artist.  Suitable for all levels and ages.

All materials are supplied and the class relaxed and nurturing, fun and deeply meaningful.

Refreshments served.

AUD30 per person limited to 10 participantsâ¦bookings essential.

Through collage art, cutting words and pictures from magazines, plus a free-flow of visual ideas from your sub-conscious, you will build a unique picture of your topic, which then becomes a pleasing affirmation for the future.

This is a totally engrossing session which provides you with many long-term benefits of direction and motivation.

Anyone can do this, you don't need to be an Artist.  Suitable for all levels and ages.

All materials are supplied and the class relaxed and nurturing, fun and deeply meaningful.

Refreshments served.

Semua materi disediakan dan kelasnya santai dan memelihara, menyenangkan dan sangat bermakna.

_source.productName: Chinchilla Fossil Finders
_source.productDescription:
Chinchilla Fossil Finders is the all-ages community event inviting everyone to unleash their inner palaeontologist and join in Queensland Museum's exciting excavation efforts.

Help Queensland Museum palaeontologists sort and sieve through local sediment samples to discover and identify real fossils of all shapes and sizes. 

There will be hands-on kids activities, mini train rides, giveaways, fossil displays, wildlife shows and  demonstrations. Plus, you can bring in your own rocks or fossils to be identified.

Food and drinks will be available for sale.

Entry is free, booking not required. Simply come along and join the fossil hunt!

Presented by Future Makers.

 A  partnership between Queensland Museum and Shell's QGC business

_source.productName: Wild Earth Border Bolt Running Festival
_source.productDescription:
Bouncing out of the blocks on debut in 2022, the Border Bolt is back and takes you on back onto the bumpy but beautiful border trails in Currumbin Valley. 

With no less than 4 race distances to choose from; ranging from 6km & 13km, through to the 22km and 31km events form Round 2 in our Triple Crown Trail Series.

A great stand-alone run or ideal prep for Coastal High; just 4 weeks later. The Border Bolt showcases the beautiful Gold Coast hinterland, yet starts and finishes by our world-famous beaches!

_source.productName: Goompi Community NAIDOC Celebration - The Next Generation Strength, Vision and Legacy
_source.productDescription:
Join in for a vibrant and inclusive celebration of culture, connection, and community at the Goompi Community NAIDOC event on Minjerribah (North Stradbroke Island). 

Held at the Dunwich State School Oval, this free, family-friendly event brings together First Nations and non-Indigenous community members to honour the 2025 NAIDOC theme "The Next Generation: Strength, Vision and Legacy."

Enjoy a rich program of traditional and contemporary Quandamooka performances, cultural workshops, bush tucker tastings, arts and crafts, storytelling, and interactive activities. 

This event is co-hosted by local community organisations including: 
Minjerribah Moorgumpin Elders-in-Council Aboriginal Corporation
Yulu-Burri-Ba Aboriginal Corporation for Community Health
North Stradbroke Island Aboriginal and Islanders Housing Co-operative Society
Quandamooka Yoolooburrabee Aboriginal Corporation
Dunwich State School
North Stradbroke Island Historical Museum.

The day celebrates intergenerational knowledge-sharing, cultural pride, and reconciliation. All are welcome to experience the spirit of community and culture in one of Queensland's most unique island settings.

All ages are welcome â families, students, Elders, and visitors are encouraged to attend.

This National NAIDOC Week Activity is proudly funded and supported by the National Indigenous Australians Agency (NIAA) and Redland City Council.

Participe en una vibrante e inclusiva celebraciÃ³n de la cultura, la conexiÃ³n y la comunidad en el evento NAIDOC de la Comunidad Goompi en Minjerribah (Isla Stradbroke Norte).

Este evento gratuito y familiar, celebrado en el Ãvalo de la Escuela Estatal de Dunwich, reÃºne a miembros de las Primeras Naciones y de la comunidad no indÃ­gena para honrar el lema de NAIDOC 2025: "La PrÃ³xima GeneraciÃ³n: Fuerza, VisiÃ³n y Legado".

Partecipa a una celebrazione vivace e inclusiva di cultura, connessione e comunitÃ  all'evento NAIDOC della comunitÃ  di Goompi a Minjerribah (North Stradbroke Island).

Tenutosi presso il Dunwich State School Oval, questo evento gratuito e per famiglie riunisce membri delle Prime Nazioni e della comunitÃ  non indigena per celebrare il tema del NAIDOC 2025 "La prossima generazione: forza, visione ed ereditÃ ".

Goditi un ricco programma di spettacoli tradizionali e contemporanei Quandamooka, laboratori culturali, degustazioni di cibo del bush, arti e mestieri, narrazioni e attivitÃ  interattive.

Questo evento Ã¨ co-organizzato da organizzazioni della comunitÃ  locale, tra cui:
Minjerribah Moorgumpin Elders-in-Council Aboriginal Corporation
Yulu-Burri-Ba Aboriginal Corporation for Community Health
North Stradbroke Island Aboriginal and Islanders Housing Co-operative Society
Quandamooka Yoolooburrabee Aboriginal Corporation
Dunwich State School
North Stradbroke Island Historical Museum.

La giornata celebra la condivisione di conoscenze intergenerazionali, l'orgoglio culturale e la riconciliazione. Tutti sono invitati a vivere lo spirito di comunitÃ  e la cultura in uno dei contesti insulari piÃ¹ unici del Queensland.

Sono benvenuti tutte le etÃ : famiglie, studenti, anziani e visitatori sono incoraggiati a partecipare.

Questa attivitÃ  della Settimana Nazionale NAIDOC Ã¨ orgogliosamente finanziata e sostenuta dalla National Indigenous Australians Agency (NIAA) e dal Consiglio Comunale di Redland.

_source.productName: Gutsy Girls Adventure Film Tour -Noosa
_source.productDescription:
Brace yourself for an exhilarating showcase of female adventurers pushing boundaries and defying expectations! The Gutsy Girls Adventure Film Tour brings you 2.5 hours of heart-pounding action and soul-stirring stories from fearless women around the globe.

This year's lineup features six extraordinary short films capturing the raw intensity of: breathtaking mountaineering expeditions in the Alps, gravity-defying mountain biking with legend Robin Goomes, subterranean exploration with world-renowned cave diver Jill Heinerth and adrenaline-pumping snowboarding and BASE jumping in the Canadian Rockies.

Experience the thrill of adventure through a diverse collection of films varying in length and style, each spotlighting remarkable women who are redefining what's possible in the adventure world.
The Gutsy Girls Adventure Film Tour offers an abundance of inspiration, regardless of age, gender, or experience level.

Join an unforgettable evening of inspiration, celebration, and pure adventure.

The Gutsy Girls Adventure Film Tour is exempt from classification, but the films are suitable for all ages (none of the films include swearing or drug references).Â Seating is not allocated.Â  Arrive early for the best seats.Â  Sorry, no refunds.

_source.productDescription:
Following hugely successful sold-out national tours in 2023 and 2024, Queen â Bohemian Rhapsody returns to RPAC for an encore performance!

Widely acclaimed as the most authentic Queen tribute experience in the world, Queen â Bohemian Rhapsody stars the sensational Thomas Crane, whose powerhouse vocals and masterful piano playing bring Freddie Mercury's magic to life. Backed by his dynamic live band, Crane delivers all the greatest hits and fan favourites from Queen's chart-topping albums.

There's no denying Queen's place among the greatest rock bands of the 20th centuryâand Freddie Mercury remains one of the most charismatic and flamboyant performers in rock history.

Following the global success of the Bohemian Rhapsody movie, this electrifying tribute show recreates the visual spectacle, sound, and stage energy of a real Queen concert.

Sing along to all the anthems you know and love: We Will Rock You, Crazy Little Thing Called Love, We Are the Champions, Radio Ga Ga, A Kind of Magic, I Want to Break Free, Another One Bites the Dust, and of course, Bohemian Rhapsody.

Don't miss this one-night-only encore event at RPAC!

_source.productName: Electric Fields â With the Queensland Symphony Orchestra
_source.productDescription:
Renowned for their captivating fusion of vibrant traditional culture with pop, soul and electronica, Electric Fields' original compositions and contemporised arrangements of traditional inma bring breathtaking moments of beauty and power to audiences across Australia, and around the world.

With their evocative works reimagined for orchestra by composer Alex Turley (arranger for Genesis Owusu, Ngaiire and more), this collaboration with the Queensland Symphony Orchestra, conducted by Vanessa Scammell, will showcase Electric Fields' awe-inspiring music on a grand scale.

Don't miss Electric Fields in this unique concert experience with the full power of the Queensland Symphony Orchestra for one night only during Clancestry.

Electric Fields with the Queensland Symphony Orchestra is part of Clancestry.

_source.productName: The New Millennium: 2001 to Now | Panel Discussion and Jeremy Hynes Reprised
_source.productDescription:
Inviting you to join a series of public forums addressing the contributions the Institute for Modern Art has made to Queensland's art ecology, reconnecting the institution with previous generations, and generating speculative visions for our future.

The second session prods at recent history. What did the turn of the millennium mean for the IMA? In a world of Web 2.0, identity politics, social media, and globalisation, how do the threads of the IMA's history weave together the story of our contemporary life?

Sally Butler leads a conversation with Josh Milani, Andrew McNamara, Lawrence English, Judy Watson, and Amelia Barikin as they weigh in our last twenty-five years.

Iconic performances of Jeremy Hynes will be re-enacted by Queensland College of Art students, led by Justene Williams.

2025 marks fifty years since the Institute for Modern Art first opened its doors in Brisbane. For five decades, the IMA has presented the latest in contemporary artâconnecting the local, national, and international, the established and the emergentâand has served as a hub for Brisbane's art life. The organisation has navigated the chops, changes, and paradigm shifts that have marked the art of the times. To celebrate its fiftieth anniversary, the IMA is presenting three public forums. The first two will explore its past; the third will imagine its future. Each forum will be followed by a performance.

The second session prods at recent history. What did the turn of the millennium mean for the IMA? In a world of Web 2.0, identity politics, social media, and globalisation, how do the threads of the IMA's history weave together the story of our contemporary life?

Sally Butler leads a conversation with Josh Milani, Andrew McNamara, Lawrence English, Judy Watson, and Amelia Barikin as they weigh in our last twenty-five years.

Iconic performances of Jeremy Hynes will be re-enacted by Queensland College of Art students, led by Justene Williams.

2025 marks fifty years since the Institute for Modern Art first opened its doors in Brisbane. For five decades, the IMA has presented the latest in contemporary artâconnecting the local, national, and international, the established and the emergentâand has served as a hub for Brisbane's art life. The organisation has navigated the chops, changes, and paradigm shifts that have marked the art of the times. To celebrate its fiftieth anniversary, the IMA is presenting three public forums. The first two will explore its past; the third will imagine its future. Each forum will be followed by a performance.

Mengundang Anda untuk bergabung dalam serangkaian forum publik yang membahas kontribusi Institut Seni Modern bagi ekologi seni Queensland, menghubungkan kembali institusi ini dengan generasi sebelumnya, dan menghasilkan visi spekulatif untuk masa depan kita.

Sesi kedua mengupas sejarah terkini. Apa arti pergantian milenium bagi IMA? Dalam dunia Web 2.0, politik identitas, media sosial, dan globalisasi, bagaimana jalinan sejarah IMA menjalin kisah kehidupan kontemporer kita?

Sally Butler memimpin percakapan dengan Josh Milani, Andrew McNamara, Lawrence English, Judy Watson, dan Amelia Barikin saat mereka merenungkan dua puluh lima tahun terakhir kita.

Pertunjukan ikonis Jeremy Hynes akan diperankan kembali oleh mahasiswa Queensland College of Art, dipimpin oleh Justene Williams.

Tahun 2025 menandai lima puluh tahun sejak Institut Seni Modern pertama kali dibuka di Brisbane. Selama lima dekade, IMA telah menghadirkan seni kontemporer terkiniâmenghubungkan seni lokal, nasional, dan internasional, yang mapan dan yang sedang berkembangâdan telah menjadi pusat kehidupan seni Brisbane. Organisasi ini telah mengarungi berbagai tantangan, perubahan, dan pergeseran paradigma yang menandai seni pada masanya. Untuk merayakan ulang tahunnya yang ke-50, IMA mempersembahkan tiga forum publik. Dua forum pertama akan mengeksplorasi masa lalunya; yang ketiga akan membayangkan masa depannya. Setiap forum akan dilanjutkan dengan pertunjukan.
